{"PLY":[{"def":"To lay on closely, or in folds; to work upon steadily, or with repeated acts; to press upon; to urge importunately; as, to ply one with questions, with solicitations, or with drink.","pos":""}],"PLYER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, plies; specifically: (a) pl.","pos":""},{"def":"A kind of balance used in raising and letting down a drawbridge.","pos":""}],"PLYMOUTH BRETHREN":[{"def":"The members of a religious sect which first appeared at Plymouth, England, about 1830.","pos":""}]}